Package com.cafean.client.ic

Class ConditionSetAdapter<A extends AbstractComponent>

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.cafean.client.ic.ConditionSetAdapter<A>
  • public abstract class ConditionSetAdapter<A extends AbstractComponent>
extends java.lang.Object
    This class manages loading and storing initial condition data for a particular component. This class should be implemented for each AbstractComponent extension in the model that contains initial conditions that can be included in condition sets.

        public abstract void loadFromICSet​(ChannelDataHolder set,

        Loads values from the provided ChannelDataHolder into this adapter's component. If there are no properties found, this will throw a NoSuchElement exception
        Parameters:

        preserveNumerics - when TRUE, numeric references will be preserved during the import process.

      • validateSet

        public abstract boolean validateSet​(ConditionSet set,
                                    boolean display)
        This method validates the current condition set against the properties expected by the current component. If the current component requires channels that are not included in the current set, an error will be reported. If the condition set contains channels that are not needed by the current component a warning will be reported instead.
        Parameters:
        set - the ConditionSet that is being tested.
        display - when TRUE the Message.addMessage method will be called.
        Returns:
        TRUE if the component's required channels are all included in the condition set.
